# Security Baseline: {{.ProjectName}}

## Principles

- Security is everyone's responsibility.
- Never trust user input.
- Always encrypt sensitive data at rest and in transit.
- Follow the principle of least privilege.

## Secrets Management

- Never commit secrets to the repository.
- Use `.env` files for local development (git-ignored).
- Use environment variables or secret managers in production.
- Rotate secrets regularly.

## Authentication & Authorization
{{if .Features.Auth}}

- Auth Provider: {{.Stack.Auth.Provider}}
- Protocol: {{.Stack.Auth.Protocol}}
- All protected endpoints must validate tokens.
- Role-based access control must be enforced.
{{else}}
- Implement authentication early in development.
- Use established OAuth2/OIDC providers.
{{end}}
## Data Protection

- All database queries must use parameterized queries.
- Never construct SQL by string concatenation.
- Encrypt PII fields at rest.
- Sanitize all user input before rendering.

## API Security
{{if .Features.Backend}}

- Rate limit all public endpoints.
- Validate request payloads against schemas.
- Use HTTPS everywhere (enforce in production).
- Set appropriate CORS policies.
{{end}}
## Dependency Management

- Keep dependencies up to date.
- Review dependency licenses.
- Run vulnerability scans in CI.

## Incident Response

- Log all security-relevant events.
- Set up alerts for suspicious activity.
- Have a plan for disclosure and patching.
